RSA attack

The attack itself involved a targeted phishing campaign that used a Flash object embedded in an Excel file. 
[zero-day exploit that installs a backdoor through an Adobe Flash vulnerability (CVE-2011-0609)]

The assault, probably selected after reconnaissance work on social networking sites, was ultimately aimed at planting back-door malware on machines on RSA's network

variant of Poison Ivy Trojan
